-- Hong Kong drawndown mortgage loans rise 7.9 pct in Dec vs Nov
-- By Christina Lo
-- Wed Jan 29, 2014 04:55AM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 29 (Reuters) - New mortgage loans drawn down in Hong Kong totalled HK$12 billion ($1.55 billion) in December, up 7.9 percent from a month earlier, Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) data showed on Wednesday.

Following is the breakdown of data from the authority: M/M Dec  Nov Pct Change New loans drawn down (HK$ mln)12,04311,162   7.9   New loans approvals(HK$ mln):- Primary market 3,940 3,457  13.4   - Secondary market   7,295 8,036  -9.2   - Refinancing2,539 3,090 -17.8   TOTAL   13,77314,602  -5.7 No. of applications (cases)7,594 7,567   0.4Outstanding loans (HK$ mln): 904,579   903,633   0.1   - Delinquency ratio (pct) 0.02  0.02   - Rescheduled loan ratio (pct)0.00  0.00Proportion of new mortgage loans   priced with reference to:   - best lending rates (pct)   67.7*  67.1   0.6   - HIBOR (Hong Kong interbank offered rates) (pct)   30.5   30.5   0.0   *with majority priced within the range of 2.00 and 2.25 percent.